SIMPLE: gild
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gild
<hw>Gild</hw> <pr>(g⟦icr⟧ld)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Gilded</conjf> or <conjf>Gilt</conjf> (<?/); <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Gilding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>gyldan</ets>, from <ets>gold</ets> gold. ⟦root⟧234. See
<er>Gold</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To overlay with a thin covering
of gold; to cover with a golden color; to cause to look like gold.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Gilded</xex> chariots.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No more the rising sun shall <qex>gild</qex> the morn.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make attractive; to adorn; to brighten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let oft good humor, mild and gay,⟦br⟧
<qex>Gild</qex> the calm evening of your day.</q>
<rj><qau>Trumbull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To give a fair but deceptive outward appearance to;
to embellish; <as>as, to <ex>gild</ex> a lie</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To make red with drinking.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This grand liquior that hath <qex>gilded</qex> them.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gildale</ent>⟦br⟧
